HEADWORD: Minotaur
<hw>Min"o*taur</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧n"⟦osl⟧*t⟦add⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Minotaurus</ets>, Gr. <grk>Minw`tayros</grk>;
<grk>Mi`nos</grk>, the husband of <persfn>Pasiphae</persfn> +
<grk>tay^ros</grk> a bull, the <persfn>Minotaur</persfn> being the
offspring of <persfn>Pasiphae</persfn> and a bull: cf. F.
<ets>minotaure</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>A fabled
monster, half man and half bull, confined in the labyrinth constructed
by <persfn>Daedalus</persfn> in Crete.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

